The Nord Stream, new door of entry of the Russian gas in Europe
The gas pipeline Nord Stream, that it communicates directly Europe occidental with Russia passing through the bottom of the sea Baltic, it has already set in service.
It must supply gas to satisfy the needs for thirty million homes.
Gazprom, the Russian giant of the gas, has wanted to celebrate the event with big pomp.
Last Tuesday, more than 500 guests, included four Heads of State and of Government, took part to edges of the Baltic, between the music of the orchestra and a delicate bufet, in the opening of the Nord Stream, the new gas pipeline that communicates directly Russia with Germany, under the sea.
Symbolically, the German Chancellor Angela Merkel, the Russian President Dmitri Medvedev, the First French Minister François Fillon and its counterpart of the Netherlands, Mark Rutte, have turned the steering wheel of the valve that controls the entry of Russian gas in the occidental net of Europe joint.
With this new gas pipeline, every year will arrive 27.5 million cubic meters of Russian gas additional to Europe occidental through one first had of 1,224 km that communicate the region of San Petersburgo with the Land of Mecklemburgo-Pomerania.
It should be concluded at the end of 2012 by a second tube that it will allow supplying a total of 55,000 million cubic meters of gas, that is, sufficient to cover all the French consumption.
Besides, people already talk about the possibility to build a third tube for the same tour.
For Gazprom, the ending in time of this enormous work it presents airs of victory.
Poland and the Baltic countries had opposed the project firmly.
In fact, the Nord Stream is going to allow supplying Germany with gas directly, preventing the terrestrial course for third countries (Poland and Ukraine).
At once, these two countries waste something of its power: for them, it will be more difficult to be influential in Russia threatening it with closing the occidental access to the markets of Europe for her.
In the decisive point of the debate, Warsaw did not doubt to compare the Nord Stream as a "new Germanic-Soviet pact", with reference to the alliance between Hitler and Stalin to occupy Poland in 1939.
That is, if the subject is politically delicate.
Europe occidental, supporting the Russian project, it has obtained a bigger safety of supply.
But the price is a weakening of the Europe of the energy, since the project has generated a gap among the Europeans of the east and of the west.
Russia has known, in so alone five years, to do to triumph its vision of a direct alliance between Russia and the rich occidental countries, big consumers of gas and with some every time more limited reservations.
"This gas pipeline constitutes a component of our association with Russia a new artery that joins us organically", confirmed François Fillon during the opening of the gas pipeline, proving up to which point the big contracts of the sector of the gas are as political as economic.
All this explains the broad smiles in the faces of the managers of Gazprom, numerous in Lubmin, in the point of arrival of the gas.
The construction of this gas pipeline also means a technical achievement.
The submarine tube is manufactured of steel covered with cement to protect it against the anchors of the ships.
It leans on the bottom of the sea, to an average of 200 m of depth.
To build it, it was necessary to avoid mine fields that date from the Second World War.
It "was necessary to withdraw or to destroy" a hundred them, "for precaution", indicates Jens Müller, spokesman of the society Nord Stream.
Likewise, it was necessary to carry the measures of protection of the fauna and the flora to extremes.
The tube is a long snake of metal that weighs as 242 towers Eiffel and is not interrupted in all its length: neither for valves, nor for stations of maintenance.
It was in the waters of Sweden a platform of control foreseen, but the ones responsible for the project renounced it when seeing that the Swedes were not very ready to allow a Russian state society to be established permanently in the sea in front of its coasts.
"In the event of breakdown, we will interrupt the gas thread in less than one minute", needs Jens Müller.
In the event of escape, the gas of the gas pipeline will be released, therefore, at the atmosphere.
But the builders consider little probable that it is produced an escape, since they have foreseen joints that, according to the forecasts, will have an escape every 100,000 years.
The control of the state of the gas pipeline is guaranteed through a submarine robot, dragged by a ship, which carries out exterior inspections, as well as through a device that circulates through the interior of the gas pipeline.
With the form of one pure, is introduced in the interior of the tube, which has a diameter of a meter, and moves with the gas.
On its arrival, after three complete days of journey at a speed of three meters per second, it supplies precise data on possible deformations of the metal.
The gas pipeline has been designed to work for fifty years without the need for any type of repair.
The circulation of the gas is guaranteed simply by the pressure.
At first it is of 200 bars and, on the exit of 100 bars.
Five companies have joined its forces to be able to carry out this project.
The leading company is Gazprom, which has 51% of the participations.
To it, the Germans E.ON and BASF were joined (15.5% each), like this as the Dutch Gasunie and the French group GDF Suez (9% each).
These five societies have created a common company, called Nord Stream, responsible for building and exploiting the gas pipeline.
It has its headquarters in Zoug, Switzerland, where the imposition is specially favorable.
Afterwards, Gazprom rented to this society, during a deadline of twenty-five years renewable, the whole of the transport capacities of gas.
Precise Jens Müller "will pay Gazprom for the total capacity, independently of the quantity of gas that really" is "transported".
The financing of the construction of the gas pipeline has been taken I finish by 30% with the contribution of the stockholders and by 70% through bank loans.
The total cost of the work should reach 7,400 million euros for both tubes.
For example, for GDF Suez the inversion has reached the 240 million.
But the minority stockholders are sure of their not surpassing its inversion, since Gazprom assumes the risk of the expenses by itself alone.
The gas pipeline emerges from the Baltic in Lubmin, in a sandy coast planted of pines.
Some valves, with 4.5 meters of height, form the door of exit of the gas.
There are some sensors that measure the pressure, the temperature and the characteristics specific to the gas on the arrival, before it is transferred to the German gas pipelines.
From the last Tuesday, the terminal receives a million cubic meters of Russian gas every hour.
At total capacity, they will be three million per hour and in 2012, six million.
